post_text:
Congratulations to KCP Senior, Maya on being named a 2020 Amplify Scholar!

Each year 15 outstanding KIPP graduates are selected to join the Amplify Scholars Program. Amplify scholars received Stipends for critical expenses outside of tuition and room & board, a one-on-one mentor, and invitation to Amplify Scholars Academy.

Maya will be heading to Montclair State University to study Journalism this fall.

Read more: https://www.kippdc.org/kipp-dc-senior-named-2020-amplify-scholar/

post_text: We're loving this video from our friends Teacher2Teacher! Watch closely & you'll find some KIPP DC teachers featured. During these uncertain times, teachers are stepping up to ensure students are taken care of. #ThankATeacher. <3
shared_text:
Teacher2Teacher
April 13 at 8:41 PM ·

Every day, you and your Teacher Friends face unprecedented challenges – and every day, you teach on.

You're still bringing your students the encouragement and support they need. You're still inspiring them to grow. And every time you reach out across the distance, you're telling your kids, "I'm still here for you – and I always will be."

We're sharing this quick video in honor of YOU and your fellow educators. Thank you for shining a light for your students in these difficult days – and always. #WeTeachOn

Every dollar counts. Please consider supporting them during this critical time: www.kippdc.org/alumnisupport

KIPP DC will provide meals to all children under the age of 18 between 10:00 am to 1:00 pm on Monday, March 23 and Wednesday, March 25 at 3 of our campuses.

Individuals will be provided three breakfast and three lunch meals.

Webb Campus – Ward 5
Douglass Campus – Ward 8
Benning Campus – Ward 7

Learn more about additional meal distribution sites across DC. www.kippdc.org/meals

KIPP DC will be dismissing all students at 1:00pm on Monday, March 16 to train staff on remote learning protocols in the unlikely event schools will need to close for an extended period for the coronavirus (COVID-19). Parent-Teacher Conferences are still scheduled for Friday, March 20.

All aftercare activities on Monday will be available at 1:00pm.

At this time, we expect Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday to remain normal school days.
